<taxonomicName authorityName="Heim de Balsac" authorityYear="1968" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Myosorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="152" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="okuensis">okuensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heim de Balsac" authorityYear="1968" box="[2222,2362,498,531]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Myosorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="152" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rumpii">M. rumpii</taxonomicName>
, but both are now normally recognized as distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
